KG name: CORS Check - HTTP Header Logs for Linked Open Data
Description: Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) is a specification that enables a true open access across domain-boundaries. More information about what this means and why it is useful is available at the Enable CORS website.This dataset is produced by a script which effects an HTTP HEAD request for each sparqlEndpoint and exampleResource in the CKAN RDF Dataset and records the HTTP headers that are returned.
